 all 46 members and spending hours wining and dining them, despite the fact=
 that, as Le Monde puts it, he doesn=E2=80=99t usually eat such heavy food.=
 (Arnault prizes his education as an engineer at =C3=89cole Polytechnique, =
the MIT of France.) As part of the club, he will receive a black blazer emb=
roidered with green silk olive leaves. Anyway, I really do love this sort o=
f drive. This, my friends, is how you become one of the richest people in t=
he world.

And now, on to Rachel=E2=80=99s analysis of the beauty deal drought=E2=80=
=A6

Beauty M&A=E2=80=99s Lost Year ( https://puck.news/no-exit-for-glossier-rar=
e-summer-fridays-beauty-m-and-a-lost-year/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBS=
CRIBERS+%2812%2F4%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F2%=
2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60=
617da42abd12a )

Beauty M&A=E2=80=99s Lost Year ( https://puck.news/no-exit-for-glossier-rar=
e-summer-fridays-beauty-m-and-a-lost-year/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBS=
CRIBERS+%2812%2F4%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F2%=
2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60=
617da42abd12a )

Despite rose-tinted expectations, it=E2=80=99s shaping up to be a barren ye=
ar for beauty business hookups, as sellers and buyers diverge over valuatio=
ns and strategic investors pull back.

RACHEL STRUGATZ ( https://puck.news/author/rachel-strugatz/?utm_campaign=3D=
Line+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F4%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSC=
RIBERS+%2812%2F2%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io=
&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )
RACHEL STRUGATZ ( https://puck.news/author/rachel-strugatz/?utm_campaign=3D=
Line+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F4%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSC=
RIBERS+%2812%2F2%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io=
&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )

So that big year we were promised for beauty M&A hasn=E2=80=99t quite shake=
n out as planned. Yes, Charlotte Tilbury and Puig teamed up to buy a majori=
ty stake in Dr. Barbara Sturm for about $240 million. And Helen of Troy, th=
e publicly traded brand developer, paid $225 million (plus layered incentiv=
es) to acquire Sarah Gibson Tuttle=E2=80=99s Olive & June in a deal orchest=
rated by our girl Vennette Ho. And yes, there have also been some small to =
moderate transactions and a handful of private equity deals, including at S=
ummer Fridays, Kiko Milano, and Winky Lux. But neither Rare nor Glossier no=
r even Makeup by Mario, all of which were exploring their exit options earl=
ier this year, seem any closer to a liquidity event.

Meanwhile, Summer Fridays turned to private equity after the lopsided succe=
ss of one of its viral products spooked
strategic investors. Osea, a skincare label doing about $100 million in rev=
enue, almost closed a deal with Shiseido=E2=80=A6 but it fell through. Stra=
tegics, like Est=C3=A9e or L=E2=80=99Or=C3=A9al, have been particularly qui=
et as they prioritize their own economic challenges. A top banker recently =
described the industry=E2=80=99s M&A scene in a word: =E2=80=9Cdepressing.=
=E2=80=9D

