         <tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"s4">
          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The inactivity indi=
cates less about the brands than the overall market, itself. Makeup by Mari=
o, Glossier, Rare, etcetera are all attractive assets with <i>mostly</i> st=
rong financials, which would have sold for 10 figures several years ago. Bu=
t the pullback by strategics, and oversaturation in one category (Rare, Mak=
eup by Mario, Merit, and Kosas, after all, are all <i>makeup </i>companies)=
 has submerged all boats. <br/> <br/>There=E2=80=99s also the issue of valu=
ation misalignment. Two recent exits, in particular, seriously distorted th=
e market. In 2023, Unilever bought K18 and e.l.f. acquired Naturium at 25-3=
0x EBITDA multiples, which seemed inflated then and <i>preposterous</i> now=
=2E But those numbers played on the eco=
nomic erogenous zones of founders and=20=
bankers and long-suffering investors, all of whom hoped to keep the party g=
oing in 2024=E2=80=94only to
find themselves entering a new macroeconomic climate that priced in inflati=
on, uncertainty, and doubt. =E2=80=9CYou have founders, and even P.E., hold=
ing an asset and talking to bankers saying, =E2=80=98Well, K18 and Naturium=
 sold for 25 to 30x EBITDA=E2=80=94and that is about what we would expect f=
rom best-in-class skin and hair=E2=80=94so, we=E2=80=99re going to wait for=
 that,=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D a banker told me. =E2=80=9CAnd the truth is, that =
is not a good strategy.=E2=80=9D <br/> <br/>Indeed, Olive &amp; June=C2=AD=
=C2=AD sold because it was priced to move at 12.5x EBITDA. =E2=80=9CIt was =
an asset that came to market and knew who they were right out of the gate,=
=E2=80=9D the banker explained, adding that Olive &amp; June wound up with =
<i>a lot </i>of interest from bidders who had been waiting for the bid-ask-=
spread to come back down to earth.<br/></td>
         </tr>
