x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">A recalibration of =
expectations also explains why Summer Fridays ended up selling a 60 percent=
 stake to TSG Consumer Partners at a $700 million valuation, or seven times=
 EBITDA, according to a person familiar with the deal. That may be a lower =
multiple than hoped for, but I hear strategics got cold feet due to the com=
pany=E2=80=99s reliance on the outsize success of its Lip Butters.</td>
